        content='The research plan is well-structured and logically sound. I have a few minor suggestions to strengthen the implementation and analysis:\n\n1. **Critic Initialization (Condition B)**: In Condition B, the residual $f_\\theta(s)$ is intended to capture the difference between the true optimal value function and the mechanical energy $\\Phi(s)$. To help the network learn this effectively, consider initializing the final layer of the residual network $f_\\theta(s)$ with zeros (or very small weights). This ensures that at the start of training, the agent begins with the prior $V(s) \\approx \\Phi(s)$, which is the core hypothesis of your structured approach.\n\n2. **Reward Normalization/Scaling**: The Lyapunov reward $R_t = \\Phi(s_t) - \\Phi(s_{t+1})$ can have a different scale than the standard Pendulum reward. Ensure that the SAC entropy coefficient ($\\alpha$) is either tuned or set to \'auto\' to allow the agent to adapt to the specific magnitude of the Lyapunov-based reward signal.\n\n3. **Baseline Comparison**: Since you are using a custom reward, ensure that the "maximum average reward" used for the 90% sample efficiency metric is calculated based on the best-performing condition (likely Condition B). This provides a fair benchmark for how quickly each agent approaches the optimal policy.\n\n4. **Value Function Visualization Detail**: When plotting the value function on the grid, it would be highly informative to plot three surfaces: the analytic $\\Phi(s)$, the learned $V(s)$ for Condition A, and the learned $V(s)$ for Condition B. Additionally, plotting the residual $f_\\theta(s)$ for Condition B separately will visually demonstrate what the neural network is "correcting" in the physical model.\n\n5. **Evaluation of "Upright Stability"**: Instead of just a single post-training evaluation, consider calculating the "Upright Stability" metric periodically during training (e.g., every 10,000 steps). This will provide a more granular view of how quickly the agent learns to stabilize the pendulum, rather than just a final snapshot.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='4d6513b4-4490-44cd-a455-6dd51a701367'



